data.text:
Pharmacy

Pharmacy at the 355th Medical Group - Davis-Monthan Air Force Base consists of Pharmacy. For more information, please visit the individual health services.

To ensure the continued safety and privacy of our patients, all beneficiaries will be required to have the military identification card or a black and white copy of the patient's military identification card in order to process or pick up prescriptions. If you will be dropping off or picking up for someone else, you must have that person's military identification card or a black and white copy, front and back. We also ask that you bring a list of the medications you are picking up as this will expedite the process and limit confusion at the pick-up window. If you do not have access to a copy machine, please kindly ask one of our technicians the next time you are dropping off a prescription to make a copy of a military identification card.

TRICARE Pharmacy Program

TRICARE Formulary Search Tool

Use the TRICARE Formulary Search Tool to look-up your drug. A search can tell you:

Formulary status (generic drug, brand-name drug, non-formulary drug, non-covered drug)

Where the prescription can be filled

Copayments and limitations, such as prior authorization

Coverage review requirements and forms

Alternative medications, including costs

To start your search, youâ€™ll need to put in the brand name or generic name of the drug and then select the strength prescribed, as well as your gender and age.
